<br>
Now, a mage epic pet with full buffs &gt; Beastlord pet with full buffs, based on extrapolations.  As of now, a equal level mage pet owns a beastlord pet (Something mages were VERY quick to examine throughly), so while you do get some nice proc buffs for the pet and some very efficent heals, you're basically adding a small melee component to the raid, which is nice, but hardly unique or required.<br>
<br>
So, let's look at spells, from L50-L60:<br>
<br>
LEVEL 50 SPELLS<br>
Sha's Lethargy Single Target Slow Spell (Max: 30%)  <br>
Togor's Insects Slow target's attack speed<br>
<br>
Nothing new here, Shammies and chanters are already on top of the slow game.<br>
    <br>
LEVEL 51 SPELLS <br>
Ultravision Single Target Ultravision   Div. Unknown. 55 <br>
<br>
*snicker*<br>
<br>
LEVEL 52 SPELLS <br>
Aid of Khurenz Heal Beastlord's Pet (Max: 43<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
Health Increase Stamina <br>
Spirit of Wind Unresistable Direct Damage and Spell Interruption Pet Buff <br>
Venom of the Snake Poison Based DoT<br>
<br>
Nice pet buff, decent heal, STA should be useless by now, and the DoT is well covered by Shammies and Necros<br>
 <br>
LEVEL 53 SPELLS <br>
Deftness Increase Dexterity<br>
<br>
Boon or any number of other buffs do this.<br>
<br>
LEVEL 54 SPELLS <br>
Resist Poison Increase Poison Resistance  <br>
Spirit of Omakin Increase Level and Base Stats of Pet <br>
Spirit of the Storm Fire Based Direct Damage and Heavy Taunt Pet Buff.  <br>
Strength of Stone Increase Strength<br>
<br>
A level 30ish priest spell, coupld of pet buffs, and a redundant STR buff.<br>
<br>
LEVEL 55 SPELLS <br>
Chloroplast Increase targets hitpoint Regeneration <br>
Omakin's Alacrity Pet Only Haste, Strength, AC Buff. <br>
Sha's Restoration Pet Heal (Max: 1250)<br>
<br>
'blast isn't horrible, but isn't great, another pet buff, decent pet heal.<br>
<br>
LEVEL 56 SPELLS <br>
Incapacitate Single Target Melee Debuff <br>
Shifting Shield Increase AC <br>
Spirit of Zehkes Increase Level and Base Stats of Pet<br>
<br>
'nother pet buff, AC buff that's covered by clerics or other classes, and incapacitate, which is already gonna be in the raid somewhere on someone.<br>
 <br>
LEVEL 57 SPELLS <br>
Greater Healing Single Target Heal<br>
<br>
Please.  This spell might have been useful 20 levels ago, but not now.<br>
<br>
LEVEL 58 SPELLS <br>
Nullify Magic Single Target Magic Effect Debuffer<br>
Spirit of Khurenz Increase Level and Base Stats of Pet<br>
Talisman of Altuna Increase Hitpoints<br>
<br>
Pet buff, another shammie spell, and a spell all casters have.<br>
<br>
LEVEL 59 SPELLS <br>
Blizzard Blast Single Target Cold Direct Damage (Max: 430)   Sha's Ferocity Pet Only Haste, Strength, AC buff<br>
Spiritual Purity Single Target Clarity Spell<br>
<br>
Nothing special.  Weak nuke, C1.<br>
<br>
LEVEL 60 SPELLS <br>
Alacrity Single Target Haste Spell (Max: 40%)<br>
Spirit of Kati Sha Increase Level and Base Stats of Pet<br>
Spiritual Strength Increase Target HP, Strength, Dexterity<br>
<br>
Shissar is what everyone will have, same with Focus of Spirit.<br>
<br>
So....  Basically, for raids, a L60 Beastlord will function as a low level shammie.  They bring nothing new to the table other than a pet, and at least mages can cast mod rods and DS folks.<br>
